initial setup:

git init
>initialise repo inside current folder

cd existing_repo
git remote add origin https://gitlab.eeecs.qub.ac.uk/40484527/csc1034-group-project-sdg7.git
git branch -M main
git push -uf origin main


git status

>shows what files have changed, what's staged, what's untracked
>use before every commit

git add .

>stages all changed files for commit
>use before committing files
>the . means EVERY changed file, change dot to file path for one file

git commit -m "message"

>commits staged files with a message
>essentially creates a snapshot of the project

git push

>uploads commits to GitHub

git pull

>downloads changes from GitHub